<h1>Examples</h1>
<p>Explore example applications built with Routely.</p>

<h2 id="basic">Basic Examples</h2>

<h3>Minimal Setup</h3>
<p>Simplest possible Routely application with 2 routes.</p>
<pre><code>const routes = [
  route('/', () => import('./Home')),
  route('/about', () => import('./About')),
];</code></pre>

<h3>Nested Routes</h3>
<p>Multi-level nested routing with dashboard layout.</p>
<pre><code>const routes = [
  route('/dashboard', () => import('./Dashboard'), [
    route('/dashboard/settings', () => import('./Settings')),
    route('/dashboard/profile', () => import('./Profile')),
  ]),
];</code></pre>

<h3>404 Handling</h3>
<p>Catch-all route for handling unmatched paths.</p>
<pre><code>const routes = [
  route('/', () => import('./Home')),
  route('*', () => import('./NotFound')), // Catch-all
];</code></pre>

<h2 id="navigation">Navigation Examples</h2>

<h3>Programmatic Navigation</h3>
<p>Using <code>useNavigate()</code> hook for navigation.</p>
<pre><code>function Home() {
  const navigate = useNavigate();
  return (
    &lt;button onClick={() => navigate('/about')}&gt;
      Go to About
    &lt;/button&gt;
  );
}</code></pre>

<h3>Route Parameters</h3>
<p>Type-safe dynamic route parameters.</p>
<pre><code>function UserDetail() {
  const { userId } = useParams&lt;{ userId: string }&gt;();
  return &lt;div&gt;User: {userId}&lt;/div&gt;;
}</code></pre>

<h2 id="plugins">Plugin Examples</h2>

<h3>Lazy Loading</h3>
<p>Code splitting with lazy plugin.</p>
<pre><code>router.use(lazyPlugin({ timeout: 3000 }));</code></pre>

<h3>Protected Routes</h3>
<p>Authentication guards with guards plugin.</p>
<pre><code>router.use(guardsPlugin({
  guards: [
    {
      pattern: '/dashboard',
      beforeEnter: () => {
        if (!isAuthenticated) {
          return { redirect: '/login' };
        }
      },
    },
  ],
}));</code></pre>

<h3>Search Parameters</h3>
<p>Type-safe URL query parameters.</p>
<pre><code>const { search, setSearch } = useSearch&lt;{
  page?: string;
  sort?: 'name' | 'price';
}&gt;();</code></pre>

